- My fuck up?
- I fucking had him.

25:48.800 --> 25:50.560
You are some piece of work.

25:50.640 --> 25:53.840
Beating up gays. Shooting kids and trolls,
fake fuckin' trolls!

25:53.920 --> 25:55.520
You're some kind of fruitcake.

25:55.600 --> 25:58.720
Wait a second,
you calling me a fag?

25:58.800 --> 26:01.720
It's just an expression, Jerry.
You lose your focus.

26:01.800 --> 26:05.280
- No, I know the meaning of fruitcake.
- Don't be stupid.

26:05.360 --> 26:07.880
Nobody calls Jerry Delucci a fucking fag.

26:10.320 --> 26:12.040
Who's the fruitcake now?

26:12.120 --> 26:14.360
Who the fuck do you think you are
talking to me like that?

26:14.440 --> 26:16.400
I'm fucking Jerry Delucci.

26:16.480 --> 26:19.040
I've fucking had it with you.
Nobody fuck...

26:28.200 --> 26:29.720
Jerry!

26:42.080 --> 26:43.960
Put down the gun.

26:45.720 --> 26:47.520
Whoa. Take it easy, now.

26:47.600 --> 26:49.640
Walk to the right.

26:49.720 --> 26:52.160
I see a nice little burial ground for you.

26:54.520 --> 26:57.720
You always had a temper, Jerry.
Gotta wonder where that's coming from.

26:57.800 --> 27:00.560
I got a theory about all this.

27:00.640 --> 27:04.440
Has to do with your uncle Aldo
tucking you in every night.

27:04.520 --> 27:06.200
Doesn't that strike you
as a little bit weird?

27:06.280 --> 27:08.560
What are you talking about?
Get the fuck on your knees!

27:08.640 --> 27:11.280
I'll finish you off right here. Get down!

27:13.200 --> 27:15.440
Fucking son of a bitch.

27:15.520 --> 27:19.840
There was always rumors, Jerry.
You heard them.

27:19.920 --> 27:22.120
About unnecessary hanging around
public bathrooms.

27:22.200 --> 27:23.360
You're full of shit!

27:26.520 --> 27:29.720
Who told you that?
Who told you that fucking crap? Huh?

27:29.800 --> 27:31.640
Who fucking told you that?

27:43.560 --> 27:45.080
Come on.

27:52.400 --> 27:53.960
[groans]

28:10.440 --> 28:11.440
[grunts]

28:27.480 --> 28:28.800
[laughing]

28:28.880 --> 28:32.800
Well, sayonara, Frankie boy.

28:35.280 --> 28:39.160
This is what I think of your
stupid fucking theories.

28:39.240 --> 28:40.800
[gunshot echoes]

28:57.320 --> 28:59.040
I never liked the fucking guy.

29:11.320 --> 29:12.640
So now what?

29:14.320 --> 29:16.280
Now, we're both fucked.

29:21.440 --> 29:25.720
Yeah.
I always liked you, Robbie.

29:25.800 --> 29:28.840
You're old-school, you know?

29:28.920 --> 29:31.760
Got a lot of respect for you, too, Frank.

29:31.840 --> 29:37.120
But you know what it is. They tell you
to go do a job, you go do the fucking job.

29:37.840 --> 29:39.480
I know what it is.

29:41.760 --> 29:46.800
Nobody comes home,
Aldo sends the goombah third battalion.

29:46.880 --> 29:50.000
You go home without
the favorite nephew, without the job done,

29:50.080 --> 29:51.480
then you've got a problem.

29:51.560 --> 29:54.080
- Am I right?
- You're right.

29:58.920 --> 30:01.520
Well, here's what I'm thinking.

30:02.880 --> 30:05.520
You see this ring?

30:05.600 --> 30:08.800
My father gave me this ring.
It means the world to me.

30:10.960 --> 30:12.320
And Aldo knows it.

30:13.680 --> 30:17.120
So, you sell him on this scenario.

30:17.200 --> 30:20.960
Me and the nephew took each other out,

30:21.040 --> 30:23.880
you took the ring off my finger
as proof...

30:24.760 --> 30:27.640
and, uh, you know...

30:27.720 --> 30:32.520
He died defending the family honor
and all that bullshit.

30:33.880 --> 30:35.760
The credits roll.

30:37.400 --> 30:39.480
What do ya think?
Worth a shot?

30:51.800 --> 30:54.040
I think that's worth a shot.

31:02.320 --> 31:05.240
[in Norwegian]
Hey. You locking up already?

31:05.320 --> 31:06.960
I thought we were inspecting
the crime scene.

31:07.040 --> 31:08.720
I've been all over the park.

31:08.800 --> 31:13.400
There were just some dummies that had been
knocked over and a go-kart stolen.

31:13.480 --> 31:15.720
Typical college kid pranks.

31:15.800 --> 31:18.160
Actually, we've reason to believe

31:18.240 --> 31:21.080
that something far more serious
has been going on.

31:21.160 --> 31:24.360
Is it terrorists lurking about again,
like at the ski race?

31:24.440 --> 31:26.720
Very funny.

31:26.800 --> 31:29.280
I've already spoke with your boss.

31:29.360 --> 31:32.600
He agreed that there was no need
to give this priority.

31:32.680 --> 31:36.680
Yes, I expect he did. But you're sure
there's no one in there then?

31:36.760 --> 31:39.080
One hundred percent.

31:41.240 --> 31:44.600
Though, I think maybe I saw
Osama bin Laden hiding in the Viking ship.

31:44.680 --> 31:49.920
You're cracking me up. Good night.
Come on, Hans, we're going.

32:03.120 --> 32:05.880
[classical music playing]

32:11.560 --> 32:16.720
You know what, Hans? Tonight we'll let
the dunderheads sail on their own lake.

32:16.800 --> 32:19.280
Sounds like a good plan.

32:19.360 --> 32:22.080
I just took some roll cake
out of the oven.

32:22.160 --> 32:24.440
Would you like to come and have a piece?

32:24.520 --> 32:27.920
Do I look like the kind of person
who says no to roll cake?

32:28.000 --> 32:29.960
[laughing] No.

32:32.000 --> 32:34.200
[Laila] Wait a minute. Stop.

33:18.280 --> 33:23.360
Little angry Jerry Delucci, ending up
in a ditch in the Norwegian woods.

33:24.640 --> 33:26.520
All because of the Olympics.

33:26.600 --> 33:28.240
How so?

33:28.320 --> 33:33.360
If I wasn't watching in '94,
I wouldn't have picked this place to come.

33:33.440 --> 33:38.320
You wouldn't be here trying to whack me,
and that fuck wouldn't be lying face-down.

33:38.400 --> 33:41.640
- God works in mysterious ways.
- Yeah.

33:41.720 --> 33:44.480
Don't look now, but Little Green
Riding Hood is right behind you.

33:44.560 --> 33:46.640
Fuck.

33:46.720 --> 33:48.200
[in Norwegian]
And what is going on here?

33:48.280 --> 33:50.320
[in English]
Hello, Officer.

33:52.560 --> 33:56.560
Just two foreigners enjoying
what Norway has to offer.

33:58.040 --> 33:59.720
[in Norwegian]
Is that so?

34:02.360 --> 34:04.440
[in English]
And where is your charming friend?

34:10.760 --> 34:12.880
[in Norwegian]
I don't like the sound of this.

34:14.120 --> 34:16.160
Come in, Hans.

34:16.240 --> 34:17.520
Hans?

34:20.680 --> 34:24.280
[in English]
Listen, uh, that guy, Jerry.

34:27.960 --> 34:31.400
He had everything to do
with the death of your friend.

34:34.720 --> 34:36.280
I knew it.

34:38.000 --> 34:39.440
I knew it.

34:40.520 --> 34:43.080
So, uh, now you're at a crossroads.

34:44.760 --> 34:49.120
You can spend thousands of taxpayer
kroner servicing justice

34:49.200 --> 34:51.920
for the creep that killed your friend,

34:52.000 --> 34:56.000
or you can enjoy May 17th
hot dogs and cakes,

34:56.080 --> 34:59.720
and be thankful somebody took care
of what you should have took care of

34:59.800 --> 35:01.600
when you had the chance.

35:02.640 --> 35:04.960
[in Norwegian]
I think I need one of those.

35:08.080 --> 35:10.640
[in English]
Didn't know you smoked, Officer.

35:11.800 --> 35:14.000
Not since ten years.

35:20.440 --> 35:23.960
[Hans in Norwegian]
Laila? Did you call me? Over.

35:24.040 --> 35:26.200
Yes, hello, Hans. It's...

35:26.280 --> 35:29.800
Anything wrong?
Should I call the central?

35:32.200 --> 35:33.240
Laila?

35:33.320 --> 35:35.800
I just wanted to say...

35:37.520 --> 35:42.480
That it's time to go back
and have some roll cake. Over.

35:46.880 --> 35:48.560
[in English] Okay, guys.

35:54.560 --> 35:56.200
Close call.

35:58.480 --> 36:00.640
I knew she'd go for the cakes.

36:06.280 --> 36:08.280
All right, well, uh...

36:11.600 --> 36:13.600
Enjoy life as a dead man.

36:17.560 --> 36:19.320
Tell me about it.

37:05.520 --> 37:07.320
Jonas okay?

37:07.400 --> 37:08.600
Yeah.

37:10.000 --> 37:11.600
Uh-huh.

37:11.680 --> 37:14.280
Well, that's good.
Then we can move on.

37:14.360 --> 37:16.680
"Move on"?
[in Norwegian] Are you for real?

37:16.760 --> 37:21.240
[in English] I'm so tired of this:
You lying to me, keeping secrets from me.

37:21.320 --> 37:23.280
I don't know who you really are.

37:23.360 --> 37:27.080
Look, I'm not the bad guy here.
I'm the guy trying to fix this thing.

37:29.200 --> 37:32.040
[in Norwegian]
Is everything all right here?

37:32.120 --> 37:34.160
[in English]
Who's the douche bag?

37:34.240 --> 37:36.320
[in Norwegian]
I'm Ivar, Sigrid's husband.

37:36.400 --> 37:39.280
- No, you're not.
- Ex-husband, that is.

37:39.360 --> 37:40.720
[in English]
What the fuck's he doing here?

37:40.800 --> 37:43.440
[in Norwegian]
I came when I heard Jonas was in trouble.

37:43.520 --> 37:45.440
I happen to have a sense of responsibility
towards my son.

37:45.520 --> 37:47.720
[in English]
Well, excuse me. If you don't mind,

37:47.800 --> 37:50.800
I'm tryin' to have a private conversation
with my girl here. Okay?

37:52.160 --> 37:55.760
[in Norwegian]
I don't like your tone...

37:55.840 --> 37:57.840
so I'm afraid we're going
to have to ask you to leave.

37:57.920 --> 37:59.720
Oh, come on.

37:59.800 --> 38:02.160
[in English] Look, I suggest
you stay the fuck out of this, all right?

38:02.240 --> 38:05.320
[in Norwegian] I'm warning you.
I'm a regional jujitsu champion.

38:05.400 --> 38:08.160
Oh, Lord.
Will you just please stop?

38:08.240 --> 38:11.600
[in English] Okay, okay.
We will continue this conversation

38:11.680 --> 38:14.320
when Bruce Lee goes back to China.

38:15.200 --> 38:17.120
[in Norwegian] Go in.

38:21.880 --> 38:23.880
I don't know what to say.

38:23.960 --> 38:25.560
[in English] That's it?

38:27.880 --> 38:30.280
It's over just like that?

39:34.800 --> 39:39.040
[in Norwegian]   Why, hello?
Is it you I'm going to see now?

39:39.120 --> 39:42.280
No, it won't be me today.

39:42.360 --> 39:44.240
[woman over PA]
That's number 226.

39:48.040 --> 39:49.760
Oh, why've you got a number?

39:49.840 --> 39:51.680
Number 226.

40:05.200 --> 40:10.520
[in English] Excuse me.
Johnny, do you have five minutes, please?

40:11.800 --> 40:12.960
No.

40:13.040 --> 40:14.920
I got four.

40:18.600 --> 40:20.120
Yeah, we...

40:22.800 --> 40:27.160
[in Norwegian]   We've known each other
for some time now, Johnny.

40:27.240 --> 40:30.720
[in English]
Jan. While we're young.

40:30.800 --> 40:34.200
What the fuck do you want?

40:34.280 --> 40:39.120
[in Norwegian]   The thing is,
I've become a jobseeker.

40:40.280 --> 40:42.560
I thought maybe...

40:42.640 --> 40:44.440
[in English]
Are you askin' for a job?

40:44.520 --> 40:47.040
[laughs] Yeah.

40:47.120 --> 40:48.760
[in Norwegian]
Things have unfortunately become

40:48.840 --> 40:51.040
disagreeable with my former employer.

40:51.120 --> 40:53.400
[in English]
Sounds rough.

40:55.200 --> 40:58.000
Well...

40:58.080 --> 41:02.440
I don't think there's a whole lot
of positions open at the moment.

41:05.720 --> 41:07.720
But let me look here.

41:07.800 --> 41:10.800
Dishwasher position.

41:10.880 --> 41:12.200
Interested?

41:15.240 --> 41:20.800
You know, actually, I was thinking
a bit more about some kind of...

41:21.800 --> 41:24.040
management job.

41:24.120 --> 41:26.240
You can't start at the top!

41:26.320 --> 41:28.560
You need a reality check, my friend.

41:32.920 --> 41:34.440
Please. Um...

41:37.800 --> 41:39.640
I have nowhere else to go.

41:48.480 --> 41:50.720
This is Norway, right?

41:50.800 --> 41:53.480
The land of second chances.

41:53.560 --> 41:55.320
[in Norwegian]
New chance.

41:58.120 --> 42:03.720
[in English] All right,
consider yourself employed.

42:03.800 --> 42:07.480
Yes? Thank you very much.

42:07.560 --> 42:11.520
Thank you very much. Have you thought
about the job description.

42:11.600 --> 42:15.040
- Maybe...
- Torgeir needs help with the staff.

42:16.120 --> 42:18.240
Like with Svetlana and Jelena?

42:18.320 --> 42:21.000
Believe me, they are a handful, my friend.

42:21.080 --> 42:22.400
That's magnificent.

42:22.480 --> 42:25.280
[playing slow jazzy melody]

42:25.360 --> 42:28.640
You really won't regret this,
I promise you.

42:28.720 --> 42:30.000
I have a lot of good ideas already.

42:30.080 --> 42:31.840
- Oh, yeah?
- Sure.

42:31.920 --> 42:34.720
For example,
the go-go dance on Thursdays.

42:34.800 --> 42:38.720
[in Norwegian]
The girls, they are from Ukraine, right?

42:38.800 --> 42:40.480
[in English] I believe so. Why?

42:40.560 --> 42:45.400
[in Norwegian] I've a friend on the county
council who works on cultural events...

42:45.480 --> 42:51.080
[in English] Cultural exchange.
I could get us economic support.

42:51.160 --> 42:53.640
- They'll give us money?
- Sure, sure.

42:53.720 --> 42:56.520
[in Norwegian] With the right application
we can get half a million.

42:56.600 --> 42:58.240
[in English]
He owes me big time.

43:01.320 --> 43:04.280
This could be the beginning
of a beautiful friendship.

43:04.360 --> 43:05.800
I hope so.

43:07.080 --> 43:08.560
- All right.
- Hello, hi.

43:10.800 --> 43:12.560
You didn't send the flowers?

43:12.640 --> 43:16.680
I'm so sorry, boss, but they came back.

43:34.560 --> 43:36.520
[Johnny]
Play that song I like.

43:37.320 --> 43:40.920
- [singing "Back to Love"]
- [playing melancholy melody]

44:34.560 --> 44:37.440
[Ingrid Olava's "Back to Love" continuing]
